    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-04-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="252" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d252">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 253.</note>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Thornton</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Fish</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-04-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 22, 1870.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of yesterday’s date, in which you call my attention
                            to the first paragraph of the Canadian order of council of the 8th of
                            January last, relative to the Canadian fisheries. I am forwarding a copy
                            of your note to the Governor General of Canada; but, in the mean time, I
                            beg you will allow me to express my conviction that there was not the
                            slightest intention, in issuing the above-mentioned order, to abridge
                            citizens of the United States of any of the rights to which they are
                            entitled by the treaty of October 20, 1818, and which are tacitly
                            acknowledged in the Canadian law of May 22, 1808, a copy of which I had
                            the honor to forward to you in my note of the 14th instant.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>EDWARD, THORNTON.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
